cies, though. It might be simpler to avoid parameterization. I need to check if methods are package-private or public in the existing code. Okay, I could use Class<?> for a raw Class method. Additionally, I'll check if the source test package, like org_apache, is outside the library. Sounds like I need to write a file!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_VNrThm6Ob8cfRByk1K3aLgux|fc_094ee4d7bb6784a10169f9d5064dd8819fbf932f82a068119b\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/CompressionCodecNameTest.java\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_apache_parquet.parquet_common;\\n\\nimport org.apache.parquet.hadoop.metadata.CompressionCodecName;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class CompressionCodecNameTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void hadoopCompressionCodecClassLookupUsesConfiguredClassName() {\\n        CompressionCodecName codecName = CompressionCodecName.SNAPPY;\\n\\n        String codecClassName = codecName.getHadoopCompressionCodecClassName();\\n        Class<?> codecClass = codecName.getHadoopCompressionCodecClass();\\n\\n        assertThat(codecClassName).isEqualTo(\\\"org.apache.parquet.hadoop.codec.SnappyCodec\\\");\\n        if (codecClass != null) {\\n            assertThat(codecClass.getName()).isEqualTo(codecClassName);\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}, \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"path\\\":\\\"tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/CompressionCodecNameTest.java\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"/*\\\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\\\n *\\\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along